nodes.text: Gonzo yellow cheese was a type of cheese enjoyed by the Besalisk Dexter Jettster and used in his restaurant located on the planet Coruscant, Dex's Diner, before his diner was destroyed during the first two years of the Galactic Empire's rule. One slice of the cheese was served on Jettster's Coruscant slider, a dish inspired by the eponymous planet and the time he had spent there. Pashi noodles, another diner dish, were served with Gonzo yellow cheese sauce.

Gonzo yellow cheese is mentioned in a Hyperspace-exclusive release, "Dining at Dex's," which was written by Gregory Walker in the style of an in-universe menu for Dex's Diner. The word "gonzo" is a slang term that exists within the Star Wars galaxy, one that acts as a positive adjective, although only a nominal connection between the word and the cheese is made in Walker's work.
